NEON_soilMAGs_soilChem <- read_csv("NEON_soilMAGs_soilChem.csv") %>% clean_names()
# Key columns used below:

Environmental Correlations

Soil pH vs.Â phylum distribution

cat("Explanation: Soil pH strongly shapes microbial community composition. Some phyla prefer acidic soils (e.g., Acidobacteriota), while others favor neutral/alkaline conditions.\n")
Explanation: Soil pH strongly shapes microbial community composition. Some phyla prefer acidic soils (e.g., Acidobacteriota), while others favor neutral/alkaline conditions.
phylum_pH <- NEON_soilMAGs_soilChem %>%
  group_by(phylum) %>%
  summarise(mean_pH = mean(soil_in_waterp_h, na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
  arrange(mean_pH)

ggplot(phylum_pH, aes(x = fct_reorder(phylum, mean_p_h <- mean_pH), y = mean_pH)) +
  geom_col(fill = "darkred") +
  coord_flip() +
  labs(x = "Phylum", y = "Mean soil pH", title = "Phylum distribution vs. soil pH") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.y = element_text(size = 9))

Soil Moisture vs.Â Phylum Diveristy

cat("Explanation: Moisture availability is a key driver of microbial diversity; wetter soils often support more diverse communities.\n")
Explanation: Moisture availability is a key driver of microbial diversity; wetter soils often support more diverse communities.
diversity_moisture <- NEON_soilMAGs_soilChem %>%
  group_by(site_id) %>%
  summarise(phylum_diversity = n_distinct(phylum),
            mean_moisture = mean(soil_moisture, na.rm = TRUE))

ggplot(diversity_moisture, aes(x = mean_moisture, y = phylum_diversity)) +
  geom_point(color = "blue", size = 3) +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = TRUE, color = "black") +
  labs(x = "Mean soil moisture", y = "Phylum diversity",
       title = "Phylum diversity vs. soil moisture") +
  theme_minimal()

Soil Organic Layer vs MAG Richness

cat("Explanation: Organic layers are nutrient-rich and often harbor higher microbial richness compared to mineral layers.\n")
Explanation: Organic layers are nutrient-rich and often harbor higher microbial richness compared to mineral layers.
layer_richness <- NEON_soilMAGs_soilChem %>%
  group_by(layer) %>%
  summarise(richness = n_distinct(bin_id))

ggplot(layer_richness, aes(x = layer, y = richness, fill = layer)) +
  geom_col() +
  labs(x = "Soil Layer", y = "MAG Richness",
       title = "MAG Richness by Soil Layer") +
  theme_minimal()

Soil pH vs Shannon Diversity

cat("Explanation: Soil pH is a global driver of microbial diversity, with neutral soils often supporting the highest Shannon diversity. 
Shannon diversity is an index that combines richness (number of taxa) and evenness (how evenly individuals are distributed among taxa). 
Higher values mean communities are both diverse and balanced, while lower values indicate dominance by a few taxa.\n")
Explanation: Soil pH is a global driver of microbial diversity, with neutral soils often supporting the highest Shannon diversity. 
Shannon diversity is an index that combines richness (number of taxa) and evenness (how evenly individuals are distributed among taxa). 
Higher values mean communities are both diverse and balanced, while lower values indicate dominance by a few taxa.
library(vegan)

# Create site x phylum table
site_phylum <- NEON_soilMAGs_soilChem %>%
  count(site_id, phylum) %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = phylum, values_from = n, values_fill = 0)

# Compute Shannon diversity
site_phylum$shannon <- diversity(site_phylum[,-1], index = "shannon")

# Add mean pH
site_phylum <- site_phylum %>%
  left_join(NEON_soilMAGs_soilChem %>%
              group_by(site_id) %>%
              summarise(mean_pH = mean(soil_in_waterp_h, na.rm = TRUE)),
            by = "site_id")

ggplot(site_phylum, aes(x = mean_pH, y = shannon)) +
  geom_point(color = "darkred", size = 3) +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = TRUE, color = "black") +
  labs(x = "Mean Soil pH", y = "Shannon Diversity",
       title = "Shannon Diversity vs. Soil pH") +
  theme_minimal()

Soil Moisture vs Acidobacteriota abundance

cat("Explanation: Acidobacteriota are often abundant in moist, acidic soils; moisture can predict their prevalence.\n")
Explanation: Acidobacteriota are often abundant in moist, acidic soils; moisture can predict their prevalence.
acidobacteria <- NEON_soilMAGs_soilChem %>%
  filter(phylum == "Acidobacteriota") %>%
  group_by(site_id) %>%
  summarise(count = n(),
            mean_moisture = mean(soil_moisture, na.rm = TRUE))

ggplot(acidobacteria, aes(x = mean_moisture, y = count)) +
  geom_point(color = "darkgreen", size = 3) +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = TRUE, color = "black") +
  labs(x = "Mean soil moisture", y = "Acidobacteriota MAGs",
       title = "Acidobacteriota abundance vs. soil moisture") +
  theme_minimal()

Soil pH vs Richness across sites (meta-summary)

cat("Explanation: pH is a strong integrator of soil chemistry and often correlates with microbial richness and composition.\n")
Explanation: pH is a strong integrator of soil chemistry and often correlates with microbial richness and composition.
richness_pH <- NEON_soilMAGs_soilChem %>%
  group_by(site_id) %>%
  summarise(richness = n_distinct(bin_id),
            mean_pH = mean(soil_in_waterp_h, na.rm = TRUE))

ggplot(richness_pH, aes(x = mean_pH, y = richness)) +
  geom_point(color = "steelblue", size = 3) +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = TRUE, color = "firebrick") +
  labs(x = "Mean soil pH", y = "MAG richness",
       title = "MAG richness vs. soil pH") +
  theme_minimal()
